You are only updating identifiers. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the identifier property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating identifier in the description.

## identifier
At the top level of the record, refers to identifiers associated with the resource, including URIs. See the "description" model for all properties.

Identifier types must be from the "identifier" controlled list.

### DOI

```json
{
  "identifier": [
    {
      "value": "https://doi.org/10.25740/yp860tc1411",
      "type": "DOI",
      "source": {
        "code": "doi"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```
